    "Html": "<p>Hi,</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for your post. It will be helpfull as this functionality is going to be in 2 target versions&nbsp;WPF and Silverlight.</p>\r\n<p>I've solved the&nbsp;problem (temporarily), maybe not in very elegant way, yet it works. I've develop some extension methods to IRegionManager. For eg.</p>\r\n<p>IRegionManager.RegisterViewWithRegion(string regionName, Page page);</p>\r\n<p>And then I add a frame and Navigate to page imidietly. So everyware where there should be access to a content I make another extension method. This is quite strate forward, yet it is&nbsp;hard to customize the appearance of&nbsp;frame, because it is&nbsp;created in C# code.&nbsp;And secondly it's wrong that creating the frame is in an extension method to IRegionManager which is rater lib problem, and the apperance is not separeted from lib...</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
